args:
Guided by Ranzal's strong will, a wind dragon
appears and does away with both the pursuing
Templars and Volk. Ranzal then decides to stay
on with the prince so he can gain a greater
perspective on matters.
As if this disorderly rabble could hope\nto eke out victory against the might of\nus Templars. Now finish them off!
The Watch are being hit hard!\nWe must provide support!
Hang on! Ol' hunched and ugly here\nain't done yet.

You think you can just turn away in the
middle of a fight?! Oh, the unbelievable
arrogance of the blessed is simply
IRREMISSIBLE!
How is this possible? He's long past the\npoint where he should be able to move!
I will NEVER forget it... I will NEVER forget\nbeing robbed of everything—and the pain\nas it was gouged out of me!
Heh heh heh... Quiver, you of privilege!\nQuiver as I shred you all to pieces\none after the next!
And you, Ranzal... You shall be first!
Stay back, boss! It's my job to put this\nclown in the dirt, and I'm gonna do it!
All right, spike boy! Gimme yer best shot!
I'll tear you into pieces! Now die!
So what did you think of Grams, mmm?\nDid you get a good sense of it?\nDid you realize its true nature?
NO! One as blessed as you could never\nhear the lamentations of the have-nots!
It's useless, Ranzal! You will perish\non the tips of my fangs!
Those without never lose, while the brittle\nstrong are slowly butchered by the\nindomitable weak!
Okay, fine! I admit it! Ya ain't wrong.
So you've realized it at last, Ranzal...\nThe fact that you will rot here!
Ya ain't wrong about the fact I'm blessed.\nI was born the son of a lord, and had a\ngreat father what taught me everything.
And that's why, deep down, I'll never\nreally know the pain and sufferin' of the\n＂have-nots＂ ya always talk about.
There's a whole buncha stuff what I don't\nknow—stuff I can't understand.
All m'life, I thought I knew exactly how\nthe world worked—but turns out that's only\n'cause I was blind the whole time.
But now that I realize it, there ain't\nno way I'm goin' down yet!

Get up, Volk! Get up'n fight me again!
No matter how many times ya stand up,
I'll be right here to teach ya what the dirt
tastes like again!
There's a ton of stuff I still gotta see and\nlearn—and more important than that,\nthere are causes I wanna support!
Above! Look up! It's a dragon!\nA DRAGON HAS COME!
That appearance... That mana...\nCould it be?!
What are you quailing at?!\nDrive that dragon away!
Ranzal... Son of the lord\nof Saint Lotier...
I won't...let you get away... I WILL make\nyou experience the disease of weakness...\nand taste the sting of despair...
Look, just spit it out and tell me already:\nWhat the hell happened to you?!
Heh heh... AAAAH HA HA HA HA!
Agito are formidable enemies indeed;\nI should have expected no less from\none of HIS best.
Look. The dragon's in front of Ranzal.
Hey there, pal. We got business?
I believe it wanted to thank you, Ranzal.
Much as with the dragon that appeared\nat the Halidom, that one is replete with\na powerful holy mana.
Ranzal possesses wind-aspected mana,\nand I suspect the dragon was guided here\nby his unwavering will, then reborn.
All that ＂unwavering will＂ stuff sounds a\nlittle fancy for ol' Ranzal, but I can't deny\nall this feels pretty damn refreshing.
Hey, so apologies for all the weird crap\nI said to ya earlier, Luca.
No worries, big guy! You actually made me\nrealize there was some stuff I had to\nthink about myself.
Oh, and boss? I've made up my mind.\nI wanna stay with ya for the long haul.
The world as I see it is still a pretty tiny\nplace. Took me a long time to see that,\nbut I finally do.
So I'm gonna keep goin' and get me a\nnew outlook the size of a damn ocean!
Ya ain't gotta do nothin' on my account\nwith all this, neither—just focus on the\npath ya want and move forward.
Thank you, Ranzal. And in return, I'll strive\nto absorb just as much about this world as\nyou. That's a promise.
I know I made some trouble for ya,\nChelle, but now ya got my answer.
It looks as though you've finally taken your\nplace at the starting gate, yet the road\nahead will certainly be a long one.
Harsh, but fair. Still, just wait. I'm gonna\ngive this whole ＂thinkin' about things my\nway＂ deal an honest shot.
I'm well. What of you and the others?
Some have sustained injuries,\nbut none that are life threatening.
I'm sorry to say this, but it looks as though\nI will need to steer clear of Grams for\nthe time being.
We'll take care of things in your absence.\nThe city'll be even better than you left it\nby the time you get back!
Much appreciated. His Majesty has been\ninformed of my absence, so if the Church\ntries anything, you should turn to Basel.
I fear our plan has gone awry, Prince,\nbut I think it's time for us to slip away\nfrom here while we still can.
We got out of a pretty hairy situation there\nbecause of you, Gatov. Thank you.
The Gran Fiore is moored a short distance\nahead. Let us take a rest on board while\nwe continue our journey.
